parameters:
Clea: You're the advanced sorcerer from the Magic Academy,
right?
Advanced Sorcerer: Wha?! I-I'm not slacking off, I swear!

Priestess Sophia: Of course, drinking alcohol is something
to be taken more seriously.

Clea: Actually, there's something I'd like your cooperation
with. This is a directive from the Archmage.
Advanced Sorcerer: Oh... Shall I show you?

Advanced Sorcerer: I understand the content. Let me go to
the noble Kasaro's place first.

Female Barmaid: When dealing with troublesome customers, I
talk about the Bulk Gang! When I do that, they turn pale and
quickly run away!

Innkeeper: This town has always been peaceful because the
Bulk Gang protects it, unlike the weakling Imperial Guards.

Drunk customer: The Valts drink beer, not wine! This is the
drink, the true warrior's drink, a toast to a glorious
life!
Hehe, she seems like a girl Zere would like.

Zere's friend: I can't believe you actually came! It must
be the guidance of the Supreme God Sol, for real!
Clea: Please tell me the details of the request.
Zere's friend: Why don't you loosen up and have a drink?

Zere's friend: Zere, my best friend, has gone missing.
According to the information broker, there's a possibility
that she was kidnapped by pirates.

Zere's friend: That's why I was looking for a skilled
adventurer.

Mage Relm: Are there no other clues? Even we can't do
anything with just that information!

Zere's friend: I thought mages were supposed to be
excellent handy people?

Zere's friend: Sorry, it was just a joke. It seems like the
pirates at the Fotizona Port are involved.
Zere's friend: I want you to gather information there.
Zere's friend: And the reward as well.
Clea: We haven't resolved anything yet...

Zere's friend: Because you seem skilled, it feels like this
request has already been resolved.

Mage Relm: They were unbelievably savage! If they're their
friends, there's no need to help them!
Clea: If we receive the reward, we will resolve it.

Clea: Isn't it strange to have such a carefree attitude
when our friend has been kidnapped?

Mage Relm: It means they have a weak relationship compared
to us!

Mage Relm: If it's the Fotizona Port, let's ask the people
from the Pirata Pirates.

Innkeeper: Sorry, but without permission from the Bulk
Gang, you can't use the bulletin board here.

Innkeeper: Sorry, but without permission from the Bulk
Gang, you can't use the bulletin board here.

Innkeeper: Sorry, but without permission from the Bulk
Gang, you can't use the bulletin board here.

A skilled gambler like Valto, the battles he has with
warriors are exceptional.

Experienced gambler: 'Miss... would you like to play a game
of High and Low with me?'

Would you like to play a game of High and Low by paying
5000G?
Experienced gambler: Are you scared of the price?

Experienced gambler: A serious match with a large sum of
money at stake... There's no greater entertainment than
this.

Experienced gambler: I love both winning and losing because
that's what being a gambler is all about.

Experienced gambler: The wager is all mine. It was a good
match, wasn't it?

Experienced gambler: I'm sorry, but I don't play games
without money at stake.

Playful-looking man: How about it? Shall I treat you to a
drink?

Vald Guard: Despite appearances, we are actually guards
here. It's troublesome that the people here trust the Bulk
Brigade more than the guards.

Clea: Is this a scout for a strong warrior? It sounds like
a dangerous story, but what is it for?

Priestess Sophia: Hmm... First, should we go and listen to
what the client has to say?
Clea: Yes, let's go and see.
Clea: Is it possible to fundamentally resolve the curse?

Mage Relm: It is certain that blood is involved. There must
be something related to blood in the customs of the Bulk
Brigade!

Thief Nora: Can you show us the customs easily...? Even the
thief gang had them, but they were said to be strictly
confidential.

Priestess Sophia: I wonder if it's okay to talk to Eleo-
chan?
Clea: Of course. First, let's go meet Eleo-san.

Clea: Withered flowers, fallen fruits, torn clouds, and
vanishing flames, they are all by your side...

Clea: This is an even more difficult-to-understand sentence
than before.
Thief Nora: I smell Perno-san, she's nearby!
Clea: Are you using magic to make those things disappear?

Thief Nora: When I brought it home, I could smell a little
bit of her scent. There's no mistake!
Clea: Understood, let's search for her.
Clea: It seems to be a request to exterminate a beast.

Thief Nora: It's a bit pitiful, but if the client is in
trouble, there's no helping it, right...

Clea: It seems there is damage. Let's take care of it
without causing unnecessary suffering.
\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Valt Region / Deep Forest\c[0]
Thief Nora: Could this request be...!?

Clea: I believe it is without a doubt the retrieval of a
memento from the Aspida Alliance...

Clea: Those who perished during the transportation of the
crystal.
Clea (I will definitely retrieve the memento...!)

Clea: Do you want me to deliver the herbs for dark
treatment...?

Clea: It's a strange request considering that you can
easily buy them at the store.

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, I was just surprised because it's a
strange request.

Clea: If it's a request with some hidden agenda, I'll do my
best to handle it.
